x(\mu)\Big|_{\mu=0}=x_0
{dx\over d\mu}\Big|_{\mu=0}=v_0
0=-x^2 \left({dt\over d\mu}\right)^2+\left({dx\over d\mu}\right)^2----(*)
x(\mu)=\sqrt{2v_0x_0\mu+x_0^2}
\left({dt\over d\mu}\right)^2={v_0^2\over x_0^2}
(*)\implies {dx\over d\mu}=\pm {v_0\over x_0} x
\implies x(\mu)=c\exp(\pm{v_0\over x_0}\mu)
\left({d s\over d\mu}\right)^2 = 0
\mu =at+b
a,b
ds^2=-x^2dt^2+dx^2
